        "text": "Larry Plotnick is the President at Big Fish Games. He brings over 25 years of game and entertainment industry experience to Big Fish, where he leads the company strategy, culture, and vision in support of our players.\n\nPrior to joining Big Fish, Larry spent over 11 years at Amazon, most recently as the General Manager of Prime Gaming, where he led the creation of new business models for game players and developers across Amazon and Twitch. Prior to moving to the digital side of Amazon's gaming space, he oversaw the physical and digital retail video games business for Amazon.com. Before Amazon, Larry has been driving the growth, development, and launches of large entertainment and retail companies, including Hollywood Entertainment (owner of Hollywood Video), Game Crazy, and Limited Stores retail brands.\n\nLarry is a proud father of eight, a music lover, a football fan, and a life-long gamer. He devotes much of his time outside of work to spending time with his family and donating his time to charities in support of children with special needs.\n\nHe graduated from The Ohio State University Fisher College of Business with a Bachelor of the Arts in Accounting.\n\nHe will often quote Patrick Lencioni: \"If you can get all the people in an organization rowing in the same direction, you could dominate any industry, in any market, against any competition, at any time.\""
